# Technical Specification: BlockVote

BlockVote is a decentralized voting application built with modern web and blockchain technologies. Below is a detailed breakdown of the project architecture.

## 🎨 Frontend
- **Framework:** [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) (React-based) version 15.1.0.
- **Styling:** Vanilla CSS for precise design control and performance.
- **Charts:** [Chart.js](https://www.chartjs.org/) for visualizing election results in real-time.
- **State Management:** React Hooks (useState, useEffect) and built-in Next.js routing.

## ⚙️ Backend
- **Environment:** Node.js.
- **API Layer:** Next.js [API Routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/routing/route-handlers) (Serverless functions) handle authentication, data processing, and blockchain interactions.
- **Security:** 
  - `bcryptjs` for secure password hashing.
  - `jsonwebtoken` (JWT) for session management and authorization.
  - `zod` for strict data validation.

## ⛓️ Blockchain
- **Smart Contracts:** Written in **Solidity (0.8.19)**. The core logic resides in `Voting.sol`.
- **Development Tool:** [Hardhat](https://hardhat.org/) used for compiling, deploying, and testing contracts.
- **Provider:** [Ganache](https://trufflesuite.com/ganache/) (Local Ethereum blockchain) for development and testing.
- **Library:** [Ethers.js](https://docs.ethers.org/v6/) (v6) used to interact with the blockchain from the frontend.

## 🗄️ Database
- **Database:** [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/).
- **ORM:** [Mongoose](https://mongoosejs.com/) for schema definition and database interactions.
- **Models:** Includes `Admin`, `Student`, `Election`, `Candidate`, and `Fingerprint`.

## 🧬 Biometric (Fingerprint)
- **Implementation:** The app includes a fingerprint verification flow during the voting process.
- **Data:** `Fingerprint` model in MongoDB stores hashed fingerprint passphrases.
- **Note:** In the current pilot/development phase, the verification is bypassed to allow for easier testing without specialized hardware requirements.

## 🛠️ Tools & Infrastructure
- **Mobile Support:** [Capacitor](https://capacitorjs.com/) wraps the web app into a native Android container.
- **Android Build:** Android Studio and Android SDK (API 31-36).
- **Package Manager:** `npm` (Node Package Manager).
- **Debugging:** USB Debugging and ADB (Android Debug Bridge) for running the app on physical mobile devices.
